TITLE: Basic Livewire Component Validation in PHP
DESCRIPTION: A basic CreatePost component that demonstrates validation workflow in Livewire. It defines properties for title and content, validates them using the validate() method, and creates a Post record if validation passes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/livewire/livewire/blob/main/docs/validation.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace App\Livewire;

use Livewire\Component;
use App\Models\Post;

class CreatePost extends Component
{
	public $title = '';

    public $content = '';

    public function save()
    {
        $validated = $this->validate([ // [tl! highlight:3]
			'title' => 'required|min:3',
			'content' => 'required|min:3',
        ]);

		Post::create($validated);

		return redirect()->to('/posts');
    }

    public function render()
    {
        return view('livewire.create-post');
    }
}
```

