TITLE: Implementing a Post deletion Policy in Laravel
DESCRIPTION: A Laravel Policy implementation that defines authorization rules for post deletion. This policy only allows users to delete posts they own by comparing the user ID with the post's user_id.
SOURCE: https://github.com/livewire/livewire/blob/main/docs/security.md#2025-04-20_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace App\Policies;

use App\Models\Post;
use App\Models\User;

class PostPolicy
{
    /**
     * Determine if the given post can be deleted by the user.
     */
    public function delete(?User $user, Post $post): bool
    {
        return $user?->id === $post->user_id;
    }
}
```

