TITLE: Defining Validation Rules with Rule Objects in Livewire Form
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use Laravel's Rule objects for more sophisticated validation scenarios in a Livewire Form class. It shows the implementation of a rules() method to declare validation rules, including a unique rule with ignore.
SOURCE: https://github.com/livewire/livewire/blob/main/docs/forms.md#2025-04-20_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace App\Livewire\Forms;

use Illuminate\Validation\Rule;
use App\Models\Post;
use Livewire\Form;

class PostForm extends Form
{
    public ?Post $post;

    public $title = '';

    public $content = '';

    protected function rules()
    {
        return [
            'title' => [
                'required',
                Rule::unique('posts')->ignore($this->post),
            ],
            'content' => 'required|min:5',
        ];
    }

    // ...

    public function update()
    {
        $this->validate();

        $this->post->update($this->only(['title', 'content']));

        $this->reset();
    }
}
```

