TITLE: Implementing Basic Computed Properties in Livewire Components
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to create a basic computed property in a Livewire component using the #[Computed] attribute to access a User model based on a userId property.
SOURCE: https://github.com/livewire/livewire/blob/main/docs/computed-properties.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Auth;
use Livewire\Attributes\Computed;
use Livewire\Component;
use App\Models\User;

class ShowUser extends Component
{
    public $userId;

    #[Computed]
    public function user()
    {
        return User::find($this->userId);
    }

    public function follow()
    {
        Auth::user()->follow($this->user);
    }

    public function render()
    {
        return view('livewire.show-user');
    }
}
```

