DESCRIPTION: This PHP snippet shows how to implement real-time form saving using Livewire's updated() hook. It automatically saves the form as the user fills it out, without waiting for a submit action.
SOURCE: https://github.com/livewire/livewire/blob/main/docs/forms.md#2025-04-20_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace App\Livewire;

use Livewire\Attributes\Validate;
use Livewire\Component;
use App\Models\Post;

class UpdatePost extends Component
{
    public Post $post;

    #[Validate('required')]
    public $title = '';

    #[Validate('required')]
    public $content = '';

    public function mount(Post $post)
    {
        $this->post = $post;
        $this->title = $post->title;
        $this->content = $post->content;
    }

    public function updated($name, $value)
    {
        $this->post->update([
            $name => $value,
        ]);
    }

    public function render()
    {
        return view('livewire.create-post');
    }
}
```

