TITLE: Basic Usage of #[Session] Attribute in a Livewire Component
DESCRIPTION: A ShowPosts component that demonstrates how to use the #[Session] attribute to persist a search filter across page refreshes. The component queries posts based on the search value and renders them in a view.
SOURCE: https://github.com/livewire/livewire/blob/main/docs/session-properties.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

use Livewire\Attributes\Session;
use Livewire\Component;
use App\Models\Post;

class ShowPosts extends Component
{
    #[Session] // [tl! highlight]
    public $search;

    protected function posts()
    {
        return $this->search === ''
            ? Post::all()
            : Post::where('title', 'like', '%'.$this->search.'%');
    }

    public function render()
    {
        return view('livewire.show-posts', [
            'posts' => $this->posts(),
        ]);
    }
}
```

