TITLE: Implementing a Countdown Component with Livewire Streaming in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates a basic CountDown component using Livewire's wire:stream API. It streams a countdown from 3 to 0, updating the browser every second while a single network request is ongoing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/livewire/livewire/blob/main/docs/wire-stream.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Livewire\Component;

class CountDown extends Component
{
    public $start = 3;

    public function begin()
    {
        while ($this->start >= 0) {
            // Stream the current count to the browser...
            $this->stream(  // [tl! highlight:4]
                to: 'count',
                content: $this->start,
                replace: true,
            );

            // Pause for 1 second between numbers...
            sleep(1);

            // Decrement the counter...
            $this->start = $this->start - 1;
        };
    }

    public function render()
    {
        return <<<'HTML'
        <div>
            <button wire:click="begin">Start count-down</button>

            <h1>Count: <span wire:stream="count">{{ $start }}</span></h1> <!-- [tl! highlight] -->
        </div>
        HTML;
    }
}
```

