TITLE: Manually Adding Validation Errors in Livewire Component
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to manually add validation errors in a Livewire component by intercepting the internal validator. It demonstrates adding a custom validation rule to check if a title starts with quotations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/livewire/livewire/blob/main/docs/validation.md#2025-04-20_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Livewire\Attributes\Validate;
use Livewire\Component;
use App\Models\Post;

class CreatePost extends Component
{
    #[Validate('required|min:3')]
	public $title = '';

    #[Validate('required|min:3')]
    public $content = '';

    public function boot()
    {
        $this->withValidator(function ($validator) {
            $validator->after(function ($validator) {
                if (str($this->title)->startsWith('"')) {
                    $validator->errors()->add('title', 'Titles cannot start with quotations');
                }
            });
        });
    }

    public function save()
    {
		Post::create($this->all());

		return redirect()->to('/posts');
    }

    // ...
}
```

