TITLE: Insecure implementation using public properties
DESCRIPTION: Another insecure implementation where the post ID is stored as a public property instead of being passed as an action parameter. This is vulnerable because public properties can be manipulated by users.
SOURCE: https://github.com/livewire/livewire/blob/main/docs/security.md#2025-04-20_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

use App\Models\Post;
use Livewire\Component;

class ShowPost extends Component
{
    public $postId;

    public function mount($postId)
    {
        $this->postId = $postId;
    }

    public function delete()
    {
        // INSECURE!

        $post = Post::find($this->postId);

        $post->delete();
    }
}
```

LANGUAGE: html
CODE:
```
<button wire:click="delete">Delete Post</button>
```

